The paper deals with online scheduling on multiple machines, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the concept of competitive-ratio approximation schemes, which is related to optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.DM). The paper uses mathematical analysis to determine the competitive ratio, which is a common technique in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the online-list model, which is a subfield of online algorithms and falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of minimizing the makespan, which is related to computational complexity and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
